This paper is primarily focused on robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also heavily utilizes reinforcement learning (RL) and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses computer vision (cs.CV) to process visual inputs and make decisions based on them. Finally, the paper discusses the transfer of policies learned in simulation to a real robotic arm, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
